{
  "_comment": "AEGIS — Verify path SLO dashboard. Skeleton: data source bound at provisioning time (uid is a placeholder), but every panel carries a real PromQL expression. Metric names come from apps/api/src/common/metrics — keep this file in sync with that module. If a metric name changes there, the panel here must change.",
  "annotations": {
    "list": [
      {
        "builtIn": 1,
        "datasource": { "type": "grafana", "uid": "-- Grafana --" },
        "enable": true,
        "hide": true,
        "iconColor": "rgba(0, 211, 255, 1)",
        "name": "Annotations & Alerts",
        "type": "dashboard"
      }
    ]
  },
  "description": "AEGIS verify hot-path SLO dashboard. Tracks the four numbers the operator looks at first during an incident: verify latency (p50/p95/p99), denial-reason mix, BATE recompute lag, and Redis cache hit rate. All time ranges are over the dashboard-selected interval ($__rate_interval).",
  "editable": true,
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "graphTooltip": 1,
  "id": null,
  "links": [],
  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "title": "Verify latency (p50 / p95 / p99)",
      "description": "End-to-end /v1/verify latency. SLO: p99 < 200ms in Phase 1 (origin), < 80ms in Phase 3 (edge). Histogram bucket boundaries are defined in apps/api/src/common/metrics/verify.histogram.ts.",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}" },
      "gridPos": { "h": 10, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 0 },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "p50",
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.50, sum by (le) (rate(aegis_verify_latency_seconds_bucket[$__rate_interval])))",
          "legendFormat": "p50"
        },
        {
          "refId": "p95",
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(aegis_verify_latency_seconds_bucket[$__rate_interval])))",
          "legendFormat": "p95"
        },
        {
          "refId": "p99",
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (le) (rate(aegis_verify_latency_seconds_bucket[$__rate_interval])))",
          "legendFormat": "p99"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "s",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              { "color": "green", "value": null },
              { "color": "yellow", "value": 0.1 },
              { "color": "red", "value": 0.2 }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "title": "Denial reasons (per minute)",
      "description": "Verify denials by reason, ordered by docs/SECURITY.md § 6 precedence. A sudden spike in INVALID_SIGNATURE = relying-party SDK regression. Spike in SCOPE_NOT_GRANTED = customer issued tokens with too-narrow scopes. Spike in TRUST_SCORE_TOO_LOW with no signal-volume change = BATE math drift; investigate immediately.",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}" },
      "gridPos": { "h": 10, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 0 },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "denials",
          "expr": "sum by (denial_reason) (rate(aegis_verify_denials_total[$__rate_interval])) * 60",
          "legendFormat": "{{denial_reason}}"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "ops",
          "custom": { "drawStyle": "bars", "stacking": { "mode": "normal" } }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "right", "calcs": ["last", "mean", "max"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi", "sort": "desc" }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "title": "BATE recompute lag (s)",
      "description": "Time between a BATE signal landing and the resulting trust-score recompute completing. SLO: p95 < 30s. If this climbs without a queue-depth climb, the worker is starving on Postgres locks; if it climbs WITH queue depth, scale the worker. Metric is emitted by apps/api/src/modules/bate/bate.service.ts on every recompute.",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}" },
      "gridPos": { "h": 10, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 10 },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "lag_p50",
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.50, sum by (le) (rate(aegis_bate_recompute_lag_seconds_bucket[$__rate_interval])))",
          "legendFormat": "p50 lag"
        },
        {
          "refId": "lag_p95",
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(aegis_bate_recompute_lag_seconds_bucket[$__rate_interval])))",
          "legendFormat": "p95 lag"
        },
        {
          "refId": "queue_depth",
          "expr": "max(aegis_bullmq_waiting_jobs{queue=\"bate-signals\"})",
          "legendFormat": "queue depth (waiting)"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "s",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              { "color": "green", "value": null },
              { "color": "yellow", "value": 30 },
              { "color": "red", "value": 60 }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": { "id": "byName", "options": "queue depth (waiting)" },
            "properties": [{ "id": "unit", "value": "short" }, { "id": "custom.axisPlacement", "value": "right" }]
          }
        ]
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["last", "max"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "title": "Redis cache hit rate",
      "description": "Hit rate for the verify-path cache (agent:, policy:, trust:). Below 80% means the cache is undersized or the TTL is too short. Below 50% sustained means the verify path is effectively going to Postgres on every request — investigate before the latency dashboard catches it. Computed from the `aegis_cache_hits_total` and `aegis_cache_misses_total` counters in apps/api/src/common/cache/cache.service.ts.",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}" },
      "gridPos": { "h": 10, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 10 },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "hit_rate",
          "expr": "sum by (key_prefix) (rate(aegis_cache_hits_total[$__rate_interval])) / clamp_min(sum by (key_prefix) (rate(aegis_cache_hits_total[$__rate_interval]) + rate(aegis_cache_misses_total[$__rate_interval])), 0.001)",
          "legendFormat": "{{key_prefix}}"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "percentunit",
          "min": 0,
          "max": 1,
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              { "color": "red", "value": null },
              { "color": "yellow", "value": 0.5 },
              { "color": "green", "value": 0.8 }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "min"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      }
    }
  ],
  "refresh": "30s",
  "schemaVersion": 39,
  "tags": ["aegis", "verify", "slo"],
  "templating": {
    "list": [
      {
        "name": "DS_PROMETHEUS",
        "type": "datasource",
        "query": "prometheus",
        "current": { "selected": false, "text": "Prometheus", "value": "Prometheus" },
        "hide": 0,
        "includeAll": false,
        "multi": false,
        "regex": "",
        "skipUrlSync": false
      }
    ]
  },
  "time": { "from": "now-1h", "to": "now" },
  "timepicker": {},
  "timezone": "utc",
  "title": "AEGIS — Verify SLO",
  "uid": "aegis-verify-slo",
  "version": 1,
  "weekStart": ""
}
